NATION BRIEFS																																												Hyderabad, Nov. 24 (PTI): An American was today found dead in his hotel room here under mysterious circumstances.																																												Thomas Redik, 42, an HSBC employee, was staying in a hotel in the Banjara Hills area. He was found unconscious by his colleagues this morning and was taken to Apollo Hospital where he was declared dead on arrival.																																												Chennai (PTI): The Tamil Nadu government has recommended action, including derecognition and de-affiliation, against 33 self-financing engineering colleges in the state. These colleges have been accused of charging fees above the state government ceiling.																																												Mumbai (PTI): A ceiling collapse at a three-star Mumbai hotel on Saturday afternoon injured four persons, including two women from Italy and Brazil. One of the injured is critical. The accident happened near the entrance of the Churchgate hotel. 																																												Ahmedabad (PTI): An abandoned bag caused a scare at Sardar Patel International Airport here on Saturday. The bomb disposal squad found only some documents, cash and a camera in the bag.																																												Mumbai (PTI): Gangster Abu Salem, facing charges in the 1993 Bombay blasts case and lodged at Arthur Road prison, has been allowed to attend his mothers chalisvan ceremony (a post-funeral ritual) at his native town in Azamgarh district in Uttar Pradesh. A special anti-terror court allowed him to attend the ceremony on Sunday.																																												 Thane (PTI): Enraged at being woken up, a convict allegedly beat up a Thane central jail guard leaving him with serious head injuries, police said. Sachin Shinde, 24, serving a three-year term, attacked Mohan Jadhav, when the guard pulled away his blanket. Jadhav is in hospital.
